      "acceptanceCriteria": "Software used for CFD simulation must be validated under a documented quality management system with traceable version control, regression testing, and configuration management consistent with MRL 5 requirements.",
      "rationale": "The simulation software has been subjected to standard engineering QA practices including version control and regression testing. Minor documentation gaps exist in the configuration management plan, but overall software quality controls are considered adequate for engineering-grade hemolysis prediction. The assessment team notes that industry-standard CFD codes routinely meet this bar for cardiovascular applications."
